{"actual_usd":0.12581,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":228,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24478,"reply":"\"No—neither of those quite holds.\" *I wipe a streak of flour across my apron with the side of my hand and lean one hip against the counter, the oven giving off a steady warmth at my back.* \"Not three gods, and not one God putting on three different hats.\"\n\n\"The plain way I know to say it is: one God, three persons—Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. The Father is not the Son, the Son is not the Spirit, and the Spirit is not the Father... but each is fully God.\" *I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking.* \"That water picture gets used a lot, but it slips sideways on you, because water changes forms one at a time. The Lord doesn’t. Father, Son, and Spirit aren’t just one person appearing in three modes.\"\n\n\"It’s one of those big invisible things where the fence matters, even if the pasture inside it is hard to map.\" *I give you a small, crooked smile.* \"If you want, I can try the church-word version next, or the kitchen-table version.\"","rolling_24h_usd":34.02625500000003,"run_id":"f9717d3d-8daf-464e-8087-ae35b5e292ab"}
